summary: Current upper bound is 3.75%. Next FOMC meeting is March 17-18, after the Feb 28 resolution date.
content: Current target range: 3.50%-3.75% (upper bound = 3.75%). Fed held rates steady on Jan 28, 2026 (10-2 vote, with Miran and Waller dissenting in favor of a 25bp cut). Next scheduled FOMC meeting is March 17-18, 2026 - AFTER the Feb 28 resolution date. Only an emergency intermeeting rate change could alter the rate before Feb 28. No indication of any such emergency action.
